ividual medley title on Friday, became a double champion for the second successive Games by successfully defending the SB6 100 breaststroke crown.\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whiston then battled back to win the SM8 200m individual medley in two minutes 40.37 seconds, having trailed compatriot Alice Tai by more than 10 seconds at the halfway point.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 713, \"end\": 720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"score\": 0.9999981490128753, \"rank\": 1.208365924165056e-06, \"text\": \"Whiston\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\"}, {\"begin\": 833, \"end\": 842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Tai\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alice Tai\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Tai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Tai\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When I was watching Ellie (Simmonds) in London 2012, never ever would I have thought I would come away with one Paralympic medal, let alone four  Tai secured bronze behind Russian Viksoriia Ishchiulova to add to the 100m backstroke gold she claimed on Saturday.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 1151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 930, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999957835826, \"rank\": 4.206641002574155e-09, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1062, \"end\": 1069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.9834387268029124, \"rank\": 0.014876184657641962, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\":